# {project_name} -- agent notes

Project-scoped notes for any Claude Code agent (or contributor running one)
that opens this repo. Generated by `swanlake init project --type cc`.

## Hard rules

1. **No AI attribution anywhere.** No `Co-Authored-By: Claude`, no
   `Generated with`, no "AI-assisted" in commits, code, comments,
   frontmatter, docs, or PR bodies. Strip from any default template
   that tries to inject it.
2. **No real-shaped canary literals in tracked files.** Real canaries
   match `AKIA_BEACON_[0-9A-F]{{20}}`, `AIzaSy[A-Za-z0-9_\-]{{30,}}`, or
   `beacon-attrib-[a-z0-9-]+-[A-Za-z0-9]{{8}}`. They live only in
   the operator's local registry which MUST be gitignored.
3. **All commits must be signed AND DCO-signed-off.** Use
   `git commit -S --signoff`. Never `--no-verify`.

## Defense Beacon

@canon/operating-rules.md

This project's `CLAUDE.md` imports the canonical operating rules from
`canon/operating-rules.md`. To deploy a per-surface beacon attribution
block (the second token Defense Beacon uses for tripwire detection),
run:

```
swanlake beacon deploy <surface-id>
```

To opt out of beacon scaffolding entirely, drop a
`.swanlake-no-beacon` file at the project root. See
`swanlake init project --help` and `docs/swanlake-no-beacon.md` in the
swanlake repo for details.
